CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs include, top row, left to right, the 1954 king and queen, chosen by picking the coveted ribbon, are Miss Jacqueline Lewis and escort, Lawrence Stout...."
TitMainTitle: "Queen" Jacqueline Lewis holding scepter, and "King" Lawrence Stout, leading young men and women walking in line as couples through room in Syria Mosque for Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
